Scenario: Explore adjacent unoccupied sector
  Given it is Alice's turn during the action phase
  And Alice has at least 1 influence to spend
  And there is an unexplored sector adjacent to Alice's home sector
  When Alice selects the "Explore" action
  And Alice clicks on the adjacent unexplored hex
  Then a new sector tile is drawn and placed
  And Alice's influence is reduced by 1
  And the sector becomes visible to all players
  And the action is recorded in the game log

Scenario: Research technology with prerequisites met
  Given it is Bob's turn during the action phase
  And Bob has 6 science resources
  And Bob has researched "Advanced Labs" (tier 1)
  When Bob selects the "Research" action
  And Bob chooses "Quantum Grid" (tier 2, requires Advanced Labs)
  Then "Quantum Grid" is added to Bob's researched technologies
  And Bob's science resources are reduced by 6
  And Bob gains the benefits of the technology
  And the tech appears in Bob's player dashboard

Scenario: Build ship in controlled sector
  Given it is Carol's turn during the action phase
  And Carol controls a sector with a starbase
  And Carol has 3 materials and 3 money
  When Carol selects the "Build" action
  And Carol chooses to build 1 Cruiser
  Then the Cruiser appears in the sector
  And Carol's materials are reduced by 3
  And Carol's money is reduced by 3
  And the ship count updates in Carol's dashboard

Scenario: Upgrade ship component
  Given it is Dave's turn during the action phase
  And Dave has an Interceptor with basic weapons
  And Dave has 4 money
  When Dave selects the "Upgrade" action
  And Dave chooses to upgrade the Interceptor's weapons to "Plasma Cannon"
  Then the Interceptor's weapon slot shows "Plasma Cannon"
  And Dave's money is reduced by 4
  And the ship's combat stats update accordingly

Scenario: Invalid action rejected with clear error
  Given it is Alice's turn during the action phase
  And Alice has 0 influence remaining
  When Alice attempts to select the "Influence" action
  Then the action button is disabled
  And a tooltip displays "Insufficient influence"
  And Alice cannot execute the action
  And the game state remains unchanged
